positions/3/description:
Development from scratch, management and further training of the legal department with four employees;
Legal advice on all corporate matters, in particular IP law (with a focus on copyright law), IT law, procedural law, corporate law, data protection law, competition law and e-commerce;
Support, organisation and coordination of international law enforcement;
Drafting, review and negotiation of individual and standard contracts, as well as general terms and conditions, terms of use and license terms;
Development and implementation of internal and external processes and consulting in the development of the necessary software solutions as well as coordination of the legal business processes of a legal tech company
